Keep this solution for fermentation for 5 to 7 days. Shake the solution regularly three times a day.

It is caused by 3 factors viz., iron deficiency, nematode infection and root rot disease.
Iron deficiency :It can be rectified by spraying Ferrous sulphate 5 g/lit at monthly intervals.
Nematode:Apply 10 g of of Phorate granules near root zone.
Root rot :Drench the soil around the plant with 
Copper oxychloride at 2.5 g/lit.
